details:
THE REASONS PEOPLE CHOOSE AGARICUS:
>> Immune Support

>> Preventative (Infection)

>> Prevention (Allergy)

ENRICHD AGARICUS EXTRACT POWDER IS BETTER BECAUSE:

>> Wood Grown - not oat grown (for potency and integrity)

>> Heavy metal testing on every batch

>> Ancient wisdom applied in the extraction process

FEELING A LITTLE GEEKY?
"Agaricus blazei M is rich in the immunomodulating polysaccharides, β-glucans, and has been shown to have antitumor, anti-infection, and antiallergic/-asthmatic properties in mouse models, in addition to anti-inflammatory effects in inflammatory bowel disease patients. These effects are mediated through the mushroom's stimulation of innate immune cells, such as monocytes, NK cells, and dendritic cells, and the amelioration of a skewed Th1/Th2 balance and inflammation."

HOW TO DRINK AGARICUS
- In hot water
- Add to your coffee
- Add to your hot chocolate
- Add to your smoothie or even sprinkle on your cereal

HOW DOES AGARICUS MUSHROOM TASTE?
Nutty, earthy, distinct. Pleasant on its own or added to coffee or hot chocolate.

ABOUT AGARICUS POWDER
ENRICHD Agaricus is a 10:1 extract whereby the extraction process was conducted using both the purified water.

ENRICHD Agaricus was grown in pristine conditions in pristine mountains and grown on the right wood for potency. We prefer to share wood grown mushrooms for this simple reason. Heavy metal and agro testing on every batch.

AGARICUS DIRECTIONS
- I started with 1/2 a teaspoon in hot water or organic coffee and then built up to 1 teaspoon over about 7 days.
- You could always add it to porridge or even your smoothie because this Lion's Mane is an extract.

AGARICUS CONSIDERATIONS
"Clinical studies are positive confirmations, but we are still at the beginning, and there are perplexing concerns especially relative to the content of agaritine."

AGARICUS SCIENCE TIME
In vitro and in vivo ABM has shown immunomodulatory and antimutagenic properties, although the biological pathways and chemical substances involved in its pharmacological activities are still not clear.
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2249742/

The Mushroom Agaricus blazei Murill Elicits Medicinal Effects on Tumor, Infection, Allergy, and Inflammation through Its Modulation of Innate Immunity and Amelioration of Th1/Th2 Imbalance and Inflammation
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3168293/

TASTE OF REISHI SPORES VS FRUITING BODY:- Reishi Spores slightly nutty / earthy- Reishi fruiting body - bitter, kind of like black coffee strength. >> ENRICH YOUR SLEEP <<

PEOPLE DRINK REISHI SPORES FOR:

>> Hormone Balance

>> Deep Sleep

>> Immune Support

>> Feel Calm

ENRICHD REISHI SPORE POWDER IS BETTER BECAUSE:

>> Sourced from Wood-Grown Reishi (for potency)

>> Cracked cell for greater bioavailability

>> Heavy metal testing on every batch

>> Ancient wisdom applied in the extraction process

HOW TO DRINK:
1/2 to 1 tea spoon of Reishi Spore powder mixed with warm water and drink as a a lovely grounding and calming tea. You can also add to coffee or hot chocolate. Add to smoothies if you like but I LOVE to drink it in warm water to really taste it.

FEELING GEEKY?
- Triterpenes (adaptogenic properties)
- Hormonal Balance
- Relaxing / calming effects
- See Note below for a warning on Reishi spores. 

REISHI HAS BEEN STUDIED FOR:

1) Supporting the immune system and calming nature.

2) Antiviral, antibacterial and anti-fungal properties (always useful right?).

3) Fighting allergies and asthma (it's the triterpenes that help).

4) Protecting against viruses and infections.

5) Defending tumor growth and cancer.

6) Reputed to support Jing, Qi AND Shen.

REISHI AS A TONIC HERB:
Reishi is what's known as a tonic herb. Tonic herbs are herbs that promote health and healthy aging through regular consumption. When I can get it, and I am in good health, I consume Reishi every day.

TASTE OF REISHI SPORES VS FRUITING BODY:
- Reishi Spores slightly nutty / earthy
- Reishi fruiting body - bitter, kind of like black coffee strength. (great added to coffee or used like a coffee)
- If you like sweet tastes, adding a little stevia or honey, nut milk and organic cacao - delicious hot choc!

TRADITIONAL CHINESE MEDICINE ON REISHI:
Calms the Spirit and Tonifies the Lung qi

NOTE ON REISHI SPORES:
One very small study found that people with existing stomach cancer did not react well to Reishi Spores but may react well with Reishi Fruiting body.

name: Samurai Matcha Powder Tea Ceremonial Grade (Organically grown)
description:
ENRICHD Samurai Matcha is Ceremonial Grade and organically grown.
Because of its high levels of anti-oxidants and uplifting nature, Matcha has been enjoyed in the East for thousands of years. (Tea was originally medicine after all! :) Matcha specifically is also reputed for being high in the polyphenal EGCG (epigallocatechin gallate) which is known for it's anti-cancer potential. (Studies on the ENRICHD Samurai Matcha page)Oh and we've named our amazing matcha SAMURAI MATCHA because Samurais are reputed to have drank matcha for ALERTNESS and CLARITY before going into battle.Calmly, aware, awake, and ready...
 
Matcha is more than just "tea powder". It's a potent source of antioxidants and cup of deep health.
 At ENRICHD we pride ourselves are as tea fans and we take our sourcing very seriously. 
As well as being tested to make sure it is clean as a whistle, every batch is taste and feeling tested by us.
We are BIG Matcha fans here at ENRICHD, it's such a big part of our lives for energy, focus and a nice dose of spiritual wellness!

details:
Ocean Bottle goes beyond sustainability, supporting livelihoods for people in coastal communities while keeping plastic out of our ocean. For every Ocean Bottle sold they commit to the collection of the equivalent of 1000 plastic bottles through partner, Plastic Bank. That’s 11.4kg of plastic put to better use. Collectors trade plastic for money, healthcare, tuition, tech, and microfinance.

The original award-winning Ocean Bottle keeps cold drinks cold, and hot drinks hot. Made from double-wall vacuum-insulated stainless steel and recycled content. The anti-leak dual opening lid makes filling and cleaning a breeze. Plus, unlike most reusable bottles, Ocean Bottle is 100% dishwasher safe.

Ocean Bottle at a glance:

  • 500ml
  • Dishwasher safe
  • 180° twist anti-leak lid
  • Dual opening for drinking and easy cleaning
  • Vacuum stainless steel insulation for hot/cold retention (>18hrs cold, >9hrs hot)
  • Upcycled ocean bound plastic baseplate to prevent surface banging
  • Easy-carry loop
  • Ice, coffee, tea, juice, smoothies, still and sparkling water — it’s all good
  • Green Product and Red Dot design award winner

Delivery & Returns

Delivery Information

Standard Shipping – UK £3.95

Europe £8.50

International Shipping - £9.80

Returns Information

We’ll be devastated to hear that you'd want to return your Ocean Bottle! But will happily exchange your bottle for a different one or refund you. We accept returns up to 30 days after delivery. All Bottles orders are covered against manufacturing defects for a period of 1 year after purchase.

As long as the product has not been used or engraved, we will issue a full refund once the item has been received at our warehouse. Please note that the cost of return will need to be covered by the customer, as we do not offer free returns.

To initiate a return, email us at denis@oceanbottle.co

name: Hand Sanitising Foam 200ml
description: Our anti-microbial, alcohol-free and anti-bacterial Hand Foam Sanitiser cleans and kills germs and viruses preventing infection without the need for drying. Delphis Anti-Viral Hand Sanitiser has a twin chain Benzalkonium chloride quaternary ammonium-based biocide with broad activity spectrum against bacteria, moulds, yeasts, algae and enveloped viruses.This plant based, vegan friendly hand sanitiser foam has high tolerance to organic soiling, hard water and anionic residues and good cleaning properties. The added moisturisers in the antibacterial hand sanitiser foam keeps hands soft and supple and doesn’t dry out skin like most alcohol products. The handy pump dispenser ensures the hand sanitising foam is easy to apply and use.Higher bacterial and virus kill rate than most alcohol sanitisers.Kills enveloped virusesEN1276, EN1650, EN14476 approvedNon-flammableNon-stickyReduced use of hazardous substancesPhosphate and phosphonate free
details:
Our anti-microbial, alcohol-free and anti-bacterial Hand Foam Sanitiser cleans and kills germs and viruses preventing infection without the need for drying. Delphis Anti-Viral Hand Sanitiser has a twin chain Benzalkonium chloride quaternary ammonium-based biocide with broad activity spectrum against bacteria, moulds, yeasts, algae and enveloped viruses.

This plant based, vegan friendly hand sanitiser foam has high tolerance to organic soiling, hard water and anionic residues and good cleaning properties. The added moisturisers in the antibacterial hand sanitiser foam keeps hands soft and supple and doesn’t dry out skin like most alcohol products. The handy pump dispenser ensures the hand sanitising foam is easy to apply and use.

  • Higher bacterial and virus kill rate than most alcohol sanitisers.
  • Kills enveloped viruses
  • EN1276, EN1650, EN14476 approved
  • Non-flammable
  • Non-sticky
  • Reduced use of hazardous substances
  • Phosphate and phosphonate free

details:
Made of the finest quality cork fabric, this convertible bucket bag is the perfect handbag for any occasion. Use it as a backpack to keep your hands free or remove the back adjustable straps and use it as a bucket. The closure system features a drawstring and a metal magnet button that allows the bag to be closed tightly.

On the outside, this bag features our discreet Murmali logo engraved by laser on the front. In the interior the bag features an internal zipper pocket, an unique serial number and a engraved Murmali cork tag.

Delivery Information

Standard Shipping - £3.95

International Shipping -£6.95

Returns Information

Our policy is valid for a period of 14 calendar days from the date of the purchase. We do not offer refunds however you can return the product for an exchange. If the period of 14 days has elapsed since the purchase, we can’t, unfortunately, offer you an exchange.

Lion's mane is a malty, broth-like taste, and can be either enjoyed either sweet or savory. I personally love it on it's own in hot water, added smoothies (even soup).

ABOUT LIONS MANE POWDER
Lion's Mane (H. erinaceus) is reputed and studied for supporting brain function and neurotropic potential.

"The two most well-known benefits of consuming lion’s mane are the potential ability to prevent or protect the spread of neurodegenerative disease and cancer." Dr Axe

It's known in the foodie health world and the science community as a "nootropic" and we also like to call Lion's Mane is the "Mushroom of Focus and Comprehension" because of our personal experiences with it. It feels like we can comprehend and articulate larger volumes of information more easily and effectively.

ENRICHD Lion's Mane is a 10:1 DUAL extract whereby the extraction process was conducted using both the purified water AND the alcohol extract this is very important for the nurotrophic properties.

ENRICHD Lion's Mane was grown in pristine conditions in pristine mountains and grown on the right wood for potency. We prefer to share wood grown mushrooms for this simple reason. Heavy metal and agro testing on every batch.

- I started with 1/2 a teaspoon in hot water or organic coffee and then built up to 1 teaspoon over about 7 days.

- You could always add it to porridge or even your smoothie because this Lion's Mane is an extract.

LION'S MANE SCIENCE TIME

name: Maitake Mushroom Powder (10:1 Full Spectrum) 'The Dancing Mushro
description:
Also known as the 'Hen of the Woods' Maitake has been enjoyed traditionally for 1000's of years.  And get this, in Japan some people call it 'The Dancing Mushroom' because people would dance with joy when they found one in the forest. Do a little dance because you've found it here?
Maitake Extract is rich in minerals, vitamins, amino acids and polysaccharides and has been used for 1000's of years to boost the immune system in a number of different ways.ENRICHD SUPERFOODS Maitake Extract Powder is derived from the fruiting body and is what's known as SEMI-WILD - It's grown on the right wood in pristine conditions. This makes this Maitake more reliable, potent and superior to others (our Maitake is not grown on oats).HOW TO ENJOY MAITAKE:Add up to 1 teaspoon of this beautiful mushroom to hot water or your smoothie, and enjoy! We also like to drink it in hot chocolate (cacao) or even add it to your coffee. Actually, you could even enjoy it on your favorite granola or porridge too...
THE REASON PEOPLE CHOOSE MAITAKE:- To support the liver- To support digestion- To support micronutrient absorption MAITAKE TASTE:- Woody flavour
TRADITIONAL USE OF MAITAKE:- Support the liver in dealing with chemical toxins- Fighting stomach, blood and bone cell mutation.- Blood pressure and blood lipid levels (risk factors in cardiovascular disease)- Support digestion in the stomach and intestines- To support the colon in absorbing micronutrients, especially copper and zinc.
TRADITIONAL CHINESE MEDICINE USE OF MAITAKE:- Increase vitality- Support the liver - Help balance blood sugar levels - Boost cellular health
MAITAKE SCIENCE:Nanba H., Hamaguchi A., Kuroda H. “The Chemical Structure of an Antitumor Polysaccharide in Fruit Bodies of Grifola frondosa (Maitake)”, Chem. Pharm. name: Agaricus Blazei Mushroom Extract Powder (10:1)
description:
THE REASONS PEOPLE CHOOSE AGARICUS:
>> Immune Support

>> Preventative (Infection)

>> Prevention (Allergy)

ENRICHD AGARICUS EXTRACT POWDER IS BETTER BECAUSE:

>> Wood Grown - not oat grown (for potency and integrity)

>> Heavy metal testing on every batch

>> Ancient wisdom applied in the extraction process

FEELING A LITTLE GEEKY?
"Agaricus blazei M is rich in the immunomodulating polysaccharides, β-glucans, and has been shown to have antitumor, anti-infection, and antiallergic/-asthmatic properties in mouse models, in addition to anti-inflammatory effects in inflammatory bowel disease patients. These effects are mediated through the mushroom's stimulation of innate immune cells, such as monocytes, NK cells, and dendritic cells, and the amelioration of a skewed Th1/Th2 balance and inflammation."

HOW TO DRINK AGARICUS
- In hot water
- Add to your coffee
- Add to your hot chocolate
- Add to your smoothie or even sprinkle on your cereal

HOW DOES AGARICUS MUSHROOM TASTE?
Nutty, earthy, distinct. Pleasant on its own or added to coffee or hot chocolate.

ABOUT AGARICUS POWDER
ENRICHD Agaricus is a 10:1 extract whereby the extraction process was conducted using both the purified water.

ENRICHD Agaricus was grown in pristine conditions in pristine mountains and grown on the right wood for potency. We prefer to share wood grown mushrooms for this simple reason. Heavy metal and agro testing on every batch.

AGARICUS DIRECTIONS
- I started with 1/2 a teaspoon in hot water or organic coffee and then built up to 1 teaspoon over about 7 days.
- You could always add it to porridge or even your smoothie because this Lion's Mane is an extract.

AGARICUS CONSIDERATIONS
"Clinical studies are positive confirmations, but we are still at the beginning, and there are perplexing concerns especially relative to the content of agaritine."

AGARICUS SCIENCE TIME
In vitro and in vivo ABM has shown immunomodulatory and antimutagenic properties, although the biological pathways and chemical substances involved in its pharmacological activities are still not clear.
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2249742/

The Mushroom Agaricus blazei Murill Elicits Medicinal Effects on Tumor, Infection, Allergy, and Inflammation through Its Modulation of Innate Immunity and Amelioration of Th1/Th2 Imbalance and Inflammation
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3168293/

name: Anti-Bacterial Sanitiser
description:
Our Bactericidal and Virucidal Sanitiser disinfectant has a QUAT (quaternary ammonium compound) based formulation. The core QUAT ingredient is Didecyldimethylammonium chloride (DDAC) which is a highly effective antiseptic and disinfectant used in many biocidal applications. It has strong bactericidal, fungicidal and virucidal activity against all enveloped viruses.

name: Wild Chaga Powder Dual Extract (10:1)
description:
>> ENRICH YOUR IMMUNITY & TRANSCEND <<
PEOPLE DRINK CHAGA FOR:>> Immune Support>> A Potent Antioxidant>> Anti Viral Potential
ENRICHD CHAGA EXTRACT POWDER IS BETTER BECAUSE:
>> Wildcrafted Chaga
>> Mature trees for potency and to respect the trees
>> Dual Extract for potency
>> Heavy metal testing on every batch
>> Ancient wisdom applied during the extraction process
ENRICHD SUPERFOODS Wildcrafted Chaga is handpicked and harvested from wild birch trees in pristine forests in the pristine Changbai mountains. Renowned as the ‘King of Mushrooms’ we invite you to enjoy one of nature's most powerful super foods! Our Wild Chaga is of exceptional quality and ethically picked at the right times in the season to maintain the health of the tree.
HOW TO DRINK CHAGA:Chaga Powder: Add 1/4 to 1 teaspoons of this Chaga Extract powder to hot water, coffee or even make yourself a delicious hot choc Chaga elixir by combining it with your favorite milk, maple syrup and perhaps a pinch of pink salt.CHAGA STORAGE:Store in a cool, dry and dark place. Once opened use within 4 months ...as if there will be any remaining by then!CHAGA INGREDIENTS:100% Wildcrafted Chaga Mushroom Powder Dual Extract (10:1). That’s it!WHEN YOU DRINK THIS CHAGA...We invite you to tune into how you feel when you drink this, really notice what changes are going on for you!DRINKING GUIDELINES:This product should not be used as a substitute for a balanced and varied diet. You should consult your doctor if you are being treated for any medical condition, are pregnant or nursing. Keep out of reach of children. Do not use if seal is broken or missing.

CHAGA's POTENTIAL:1) Chaga has been studied for its anti-viral, anti-cancer, anti-fungal, anti-allergic, anti-malarial, and anti-tumor properties. This is good because it may help you avoid or fight the above.2) Chaga is LOADED with antioxidants (with an exceptional ORAC value, it beats almost all other foods).3) Chaga may help with stomach issues including IBS, ulcers and gastritis.4) Chaga has been consumed for thousands of years because of these potential health benefits.5) Chaga contains ample melanin, reported to be a gene protector and DNA repairer.
MEDICAL NOTES: One should be aware of taking Chaga in conjunction with immune suppressing medicines, the effects of which Chaga may negate. Additionally, consuming Chaga mushroom in combination with blood-thinning medications may magnify their effects. Chaga may also interact with diabetes medications, which may cause blood sugar levels to fall too low. Some sources also warn about high levels oxalates in chaga - and that if someone has existing kidney issues should speak with their doctor. DISCLAIMER: You should not rely on this information as a substitute for, nor does it replace, professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns or questions about your health, you should always consult with a physician or other healthcare professional.
Consult your doctor before consuming chaga.CHAGA SOURCES AND SCIENCE:https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2681140/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22819687https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22135889https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2895696/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1193547/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26210065https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26853962http://www.fengshuilondon.net/health/chaga-mushrooms-health-benefits-of-chagahttps://www.uaf.edu/files/olli/Chaga-Powerpoint.pdf

ENRICHD SUPERFOODS Wildcrafted Chaga is handpicked and harvested from wild birch trees in pristine forests in the pristine Changbai mountains. Renowned as the ‘King of Mushrooms’ we invite you to enjoy one of nature's most powerful super foods! 

Our Wild Chaga is of exceptional quality and ethically picked at the right times in the season to maintain the health of the tree.

HOW TO DRINK CHAGA:
Chaga Powder: Add 1/4 to 1 teaspoons of this Chaga Extract powder to hot water, coffee or even make yourself a delicious hot choc Chaga elixir by combining it with your favorite milk, maple syrup and perhaps a pinch of pink salt.

CHAGA STORAGE:
Store in a cool, dry and dark place. Once opened use within 4 months ...as if there will be any remaining by then!

CHAGA INGREDIENTS:
100% Wildcrafted Chaga Mushroom Powder Dual Extract (10:1). That’s it!

WHEN YOU DRINK THIS CHAGA...
We invite you to tune into how you feel when you drink this, really notice what changes are going on for you!

DRINKING GUIDELINES:
This product should not be used as a substitute for a balanced and varied diet. You should consult your doctor if you are being treated for any medical condition, are pregnant or nursing. Keep out of reach of children. Do not use if seal is broken or missing.

CHAGA's POTENTIAL:
1) Chaga has been studied for its anti-viral, anti-cancer, anti-fungal, anti-allergic, anti-malarial, and anti-tumor properties. This is good because it may help you avoid or fight the above.

2) Chaga is LOADED with antioxidants (with an exceptional ORAC value, it beats almost all other foods).

3) Chaga may help with stomach issues including IBS, ulcers and gastritis.

4) Chaga has been consumed for thousands of years because of these potential health benefits.

5) Chaga contains ample melanin, reported to be a gene protector and DNA repairer.

MEDICAL NOTES: One should be aware of taking Chaga in conjunction with immune suppressing medicines, the effects of which Chaga may negate. Additionally, consuming Chaga mushroom in combination with blood-thinning medications may magnify their effects. Chaga may also interact with diabetes medications, which may cause blood sugar levels to fall too low. Some sources also warn about high levels oxalates in chaga - and that if someone has existing kidney issues should speak with their doctor. 

DISCLAIMER: You should not rely on this information as a substitute for, nor does it replace, professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. If you have any concerns or questions about your health, you should always consult with a physician or other healthcare professional.

Consult your doctor before consuming chaga.

name: Ethcs -  primary
Green Tea (Taiwanese) Organic
description:
This is a high grade Taiwanese Green Tea sourced from some of the cleanest mountains and is grown to organic standards.
ENRICHD stands for the highest integrity when it comes to all of our foods and sourcing, especially our teas.
We have a limited amount of this tea (around 10 bags).Tea is something we LOVE here at ENRICHD so take extra measures to make sure this is the TASTIEST, highest quality and cleanest available.
ABOUT THIS TEA:
- Light and uplifting
- Leans towards oolong flavours / feelingsHOW TO PREPARE THIS TEA:1) Use approximately 1 tablespoon of tea.Add more or less depending on how strong you like your green tea.2) Rinse the leaves in warm (less than boiling) water.Literally leave the water on the leaves for a few seconds, then give that water to your garden.3) Steep the leaves for approximately 1 minute in about 250ml of water with hot water around 85C (185F), and serve yourself and share with friends.Ideally use a tea pot or side-handle tea pot. A tea strainer or cafetiere will work too.TEA STEEPING TIPS:1) If you like your tea strong add more leaves and or increase the steeping time.2) You can steep each serving of these leaves more than once.3) Give yourself a minute to enjoy these leaves in silence if you can...5) Drink within a minute or so of steeping, green tea ideally should be a green-like colour (brown often means it has been burned or overly oxidized).
details:
This is a high grade Taiwanese Green Tea sourced from some of the cleanest mountains and is grown to organic standards.

ENRICHD stands for the highest integrity when it comes to all of our foods and sourcing, especially our teas.

We have a limited amount of this tea (around 10 bags).

Tea is something we LOVE here at ENRICHD so take extra measures to make sure this is the TASTIEST, highest quality and cleanest available.

ABOUT THIS TEA:

- Light and uplifting

- Leans towards oolong flavours / feelings

HOW TO PREPARE THIS TEA:
1) Use approximately 1 tablespoon of tea.
Add more or less depending on how strong you like your green tea.

2) Rinse the leaves in warm (less than boiling) water.
Literally leave the water on the leaves for a few seconds, then give that water to your garden.

3) Steep the leaves for approximately 1 minute in about 250ml of water with hot water around 85C (185F), and serve yourself and share with friends.

Ideally use a tea pot or side-handle tea pot. A tea strainer or cafetiere will work too.

TEA STEEPING TIPS:
1) If you like your tea strong add more leaves and or increase the steeping time.

2) You can steep each serving of these leaves more than once.

3) Give yourself a minute to enjoy these leaves in silence if you can...

5) Drink within a minute or so of steeping, green tea ideally should be a green-like colour (brown often means it has been burned or overly oxidized).

details:
The Ocean Bottle’s flawless design makes it the perfect companion to avoid single-use plastic every day forever. Not to mention your ticket to becoming part of a movement dedicated to saving our oceans.

Impact:

With the sale of every Ocean Bottle we fund the collection of 11.4kg of plastic, equivalent to 1000 bottles before it enters the ocean, and improve social mobility at the same time.

With the help of partners Plastic Bank, funds go to places where plastic pollution is worst and tackle the 22mkgs of plastic pouring into the ocean each day.  Locals exchange plastic waste for digital tokens to spend on tuition, healthcare, tech goods, microfinance or money all via blockchain technology.

Features:

The Ocean bottle has been designed to last a lifetime, but don't take our word for it:  "If Apple designed a drinks container for life it would look like this." The Times, August 2020

Award-winning key features:

  • 500ml / 250g
  • Dishwasher safe
  • Dual opening for pouring drinks, ice and easy clean
  • Stainless steel Insulation for hot and cold drinks
  • Up-cycled ocean-bound plastic
  • Anti-leak
  • Easy carry loop

Return and Warranty Info

We’ll be devastated to hear that you'd want to return your Ocean Bottle! But will happily exchange your bottle for a different one or refund you. We accept returns up to 30 days after delivery. All Bottles orders are covered against manufacturing defects for a period of 1 year after purchase.

As long as the product has not been used or engraved, we will issue a full refund once the item has been received at our warehouse. Please note that the cost of return will need to be covered by the customer, as we do not offer free returns.

To initiate a return, email us at ahoy@theoceanbottle.com 

Delievery methods and costs

Standard - £2.95

Next Day - £6.9

Express - £7.5

International - £10

Free shipping threshold amount - £40

name: Baby Pull On Leggings
description:
PRODUCT DETAILS
ONE LEG AT A TIME.
For whizzing walkers and crawling toddlers, to babies in arms, Boody Baby leggings are super soft, comfy and durable. Allowing for full movement, our stretchy fabric and elasticated waistband covers nappy bums and is gentle around little tums. Lightweight, and rolling up wonderfully small a spare pair pack easily in any nappy bag.
Why Bamboo?
Why Bamboo Baby Pants?
Boody is all about affordable luxury, crafting everyday essentials from viscose derived from bamboo. The result is a silky smooth base layer that keeps you cool and comfortable with seam-free stretch. Our bamboo fabric maintains its shape and is great for sensitive skin. Bamboo fibers are naturally smooth and round with no sharp spurs to irritate skin.  Your baby's sensitive skin requires a delicate touch.  Boody Baby has you covered.
FABRIC & CARE


Care: Machine wash and dry according to instructions on the care label using a mild, eco-friendly laundry detergent.
Content: 95% viscose made from organically grown bamboo, 5% elastane

Harvested in FSC-certified fields in the Sichuan Province of China, our organically grown bamboo is used to create our signature soft and durable fabric. Boody is naturally breathable, antibacterial, thermo-regulating and hypoallergenic for pure comfort all day long.

name: Shou Puerh Tea "Superior Earth" (Organic)
description:
"Superior Earth" Shou Puerh Tea, we find this organically grown tea smooth, deep and grounding. Shou Puerh is regarded as warming in nature and is respected throughout the world.This is fantastic LOOSE LEAF SHOU PUERH tea is sourced from some of the cleanest mountains in China and is grown to organic standards. It is ideally enjoyed a little after a meal though can be drank at any time.Because of the fermentation this tea is naturally lower in caffeine than you'd expect.

 
TASTE OF SHOU PUERH
>> Earthy and Smooth
This is a deep earthy tea, unlike green tea because it fermented for weeks in a specific environment for supporting the aging of the tea. Shoud puerh became a "new" category of tea after years of trying to speed up the aging process of sheng puerh tea. Shou Puerh could be thought of as a magnificent accident.
WHY SHOU PUERH?
- Grounding in Nature
- Digestive Support
- Calming in Nature
- Support the metabolism
 
ENRICHD CLEAN TEASENRICHD always stands for the highest integrity when it comes to all of our foods and sourcing. Tea is something we LOVE here and so we take extra measures to make sure this is some of the cleanest tea available.SERVING1) Use approximately 1 tablespoon of tea.Add more or less depending on how you like your tea.2) Rinse the leaves in hot (just less than boiling) water.Literally leave the water on the leaves for a few seconds, then give that water to your garden.3) Steep the leaves in about 1/2 pint of water, and serve yourself and friends.Ideally use tea pot or side-handle tea pot but a strainer or cafetiere will work too. OR even loose in the bowl (see photos)STEEPING TIPS1) If you like your tea strong add more leaves and or increase the steeping time.2) You can steep each serving of these leaves more than once.3) Give yourself a minute to enjoy these leaves in silence if you can...
details:
"Superior Earth" Shou Puerh Tea, we find this organically grown tea smooth, deep and grounding. Shou Puerh is regarded as warming in nature and is respected throughout the world.

This is fantastic LOOSE LEAF SHOU PUERH tea is sourced from some of the cleanest mountains in China and is grown to organic standards. It is ideally enjoyed a little after a meal though can be drank at any time.

Because of the fermentation this tea is naturally lower in caffeine than you'd expect.

 

TASTE OF SHOU PUERH

>> Earthy and Smooth

This is a deep earthy tea, unlike green tea because it fermented for weeks in a specific environment for supporting the aging of the tea. Shoud puerh became a "new" category of tea after years of trying to speed up the aging process of sheng puerh tea. Shou Puerh could be thought of as a magnificent accident.

WHY SHOU PUERH?

- Grounding in Nature

- Digestive Support

- Calming in Nature

- Support the metabolism

 

ENRICHD CLEAN TEAS
ENRICHD always stands for the highest integrity when it comes to all of our foods and sourcing. Tea is something we LOVE here and so we take extra measures to make sure this is some of the cleanest tea available.

SERVING
1) Use approximately 1 tablespoon of tea.
Add more or less depending on how you like your tea.

2) Rinse the leaves in hot (just less than boiling) water.
Literally leave the water on the leaves for a few seconds, then give that water to your garden.

3) Steep the leaves in about 1/2 pint of water, and serve yourself and friends.
Ideally use tea pot or side-handle tea pot but a strainer or cafetiere will work too. OR even loose in the bowl (see photos)

STEEPING TIPS
1) If you like your tea strong add more leaves and or increase the steeping time.

2) You can steep each serving of these leaves more than once.

3) Give yourself a minute to enjoy these leaves in silence if you can...

name: Drain Cleaner & Maintainer (Tube of 10)
description:
Our Eco Drain Cleaner and Maintainer is a powerful enzyme treatment, specially developed to eat away at tough drain blockages in your home. This hardworking drain cleaner releases millions of beneficial bacteria to speed up the biodegradation of food, grease and organic waste to remove blockages and smells. Each Drain Cleaner & Maintainer tube has 10 x 4g tablets.
As a plant based, vegan friendly, Eco Drain Cleaner and Maintainer, it has a non-corrosive formula so is safe on all plumbing and in septic tanks. Avoid recurring drain blockages by using this drain maintainer regularly (as directed) and keep your drains free of build ups, blockages and those nasty unwanted smells.

Digests grease and other wastes 
Eco Drain Cleaner to unblock drains
Stops Smells
Safe for all plumbing
Enzyme producing bacteria
Reduced use of hazardous substances 
Phosphate and phosphonate free
Safe in septic tanks if used as directed 
Highly biodegradable

Areas of Use

Bathroom Drains
Kitchen Drains
Toilets
Septic Tanks

Instructions for Use 

Drain maintenance: Dissolve one tablet into a sink or bucket with 4-5 litres of tepid water. Remove the sink plug or pour the solution evenly into all drain pipes.
Toilets: Dissolve one tablet into a toilet bowl and flush.
Septic Tanks: For maintenance, use one tablet per month for each tank capacity of 4,500 litres.

100% Made in Britain

Ethical & Eco Friendly Sustainable Cleaning 
Highly Biodegradable Ingredients
B Corp Certified
Never Tested on Animals
Pet Safe

name: Face Masks - Black
description:
Our pack of three black face masks are designed to protect and be comfortable. These highly engineered three-layer reusable and washable face masks, with SILVERPLUS® technology provide protection against the transmission of infectious airborne molecules. 
The outer layer of the face mask is treated with an antimicrobial and water repellent finish, to kill any microbes on the surface from touching or breathing. The weave of the face masks offer great filterability, without compromising the ease of breathing.
Please Note:  Black Masks come with Ear Loop applications.   
Our mask’s inner layer has a mesh ply filter, made from 100% Polyester, an inherently hydrophobic material. The 2.4mm thick needle punched non-woven filter stops particles greater than 5 microns and offers barrier properties of 75% and higher. This filter layer provides the primary filtration of our face masks. 
For a soft finish to provide maximum comfort for the user. The inner ply of our Face Masks is knitted in a non-chemically tested polyester to suit all skin types and provide the highest air permeability needed for breathing. 

Pack of three reusable face masks, 10 filters and storage pouch which can also be used as a mask washing bag. 
Our black face masks are made from 40% recycled plastic water bottles and come in a pouch made from 100% recycled plastic water bottles.
Washable Face Masks with ear loops, designed for protection and comfort.
Three layered thick black face masks in two sizes - Medium & Large. 
Face masks are silver coated with a water repellent outer layer giving natural antimicrobial double action protection. 
Black masks with 2.4mm non-woven polyester internal filter tested to ISO 14644, stops particles greater than 5 microns.
Soft inner layer giving a third layer of protection and maximum comfort. Tested for all skin types and provides the highest air permeability needed for breathing.






You can purchase spare mask filters here.

name: Face Masks - White
description:
Our pack of three white face masks are designed to protect and be comfortable. These highly engineered three-layer reusable and washable face masks, with SILVERPLUS® technology provide protection against the transmission of infectious airborne molecules. 
The outer layer of the face mask is treated with an antimicrobial and water repellent finish, to kill any microbes on the surface from touching or breathing. The weave of the face masks offer great filterability, without compromising the ease of breathing.
Please Note:  White Masks come with Head Loop application.   
Our mask’s inner layer has a mesh ply filter, made from 100% Polyester, an inherently hydrophobic material. The 2.4mm thick needle punched non-woven filter stops particles greater than 5 microns and offers barrier properties of 75% and higher. This filter layer provides the primary filtration of our face masks. 
For a soft finish to provide maximum comfort for the user. The inner ply of our face masks is knitted in a non-chemically tested polyester to suit all skin types and provide the highest air permeability needed for breathing.

Pack of three reusable face masks, 10 filters and storage pouch which can also be used as a mask washing bag. 
Our white face masks are made from 40% recycled plastic water bottles and come in a pouch made from 100% recycled plastic water bottles.
Washable Face Masks with ear loops, designed for protection and comfort.
Three layered thick white face masks in two sizes - Medium & Large. 
Face masks are silver coated with a water repellent outer layer giving natural antimicrobial double action protection. 
White masks with 2.4mm non-woven polyester internal filter tested to ISO 14644, stops particles greater than 5 microns.
Soft inner layer giving a third layer of protection and maximum comfort. Tested for all skin types and provides the highest air permeability needed for breathing.






You can purchase spare mask filters here.

name: Floor & Surface Lemon Gel Cleaner 700ml
description:
Our EU Ecolabel accredited Multi Floor & Surface Gel Cleaner is ideal for mopping and general surface cleaning. This eco floor cleaner and surface cleaner polishes to a shine and leaves your home clean and fresh with a delightful lemon fragrance. 
As a plant based, vegan friendly, eco floor cleaner and surface cleaner, it is suitable for hardwood floors, tile floors, laminate floors, slate and vinyl flooring. You can also use this eco friendly floor cleaner as a general surface cleaner across worktops, cabinets, sinks, tiles, doors and kitchen appliances. 

Free from: Chrlorine Bleaches, Solvents, Formaldehyde, perfume and dyes, Lanolin, EDTAs, APEs and low VOCs
Powerful degreaser
Citrus fresh odour leaves a light fragrance
Polishes to a shine
Safe in septic tanks if used as directed
Reduced impact on aquatic life
Reduced use of hazardous substances
Phosphate and phosphonate free
Safe in septic tanks if used as directed

Areas of Use

Hard Floors - Tiles, hardwood, laminate, slate and vinyl flooring.
Kitchen Work Surfaces - Cabinets, worktops, sinks and tiles.
Kitchen appliances. 

Instructions for Use 
Apply a small amount to a damp cloth and wipe the surface. For heavy cleaning, apply directly onto the surface, leave to stand and wipe clean. 
For larger areas use a mop and bucket, we recommend diluting 3L of water with 30ml of Floor Cleaner.  
This product is also available in a 5 Litre Floor & Surface Gel Cleaner size. 

Loved by Professionals, Approved by the Planet
100% Made in Britain
Vegan Friendly, Natural Plant Based Cleaning Product
Ethical & Eco Friendly Sustainable Cleaning 
Highly Biodegradable Ingredients
B Corp Certified
Never Tested on Animals
Pet Safe
100% Recycled & Recyclable Plastic Bottle Packaging

Matcha comin’ at ya! Can’t decide which PureChimp matcha tea is your favourite?

Ingredients for cinnamon matcha: 86% finely ground matcha green tea leaves (ceremonial grade), 14% cinnamon (true).
Suitable for vegans. 35mg of caffeine per serving

name: Rooibos Matcha Tea
description:
Naturally caffeine-free
Made from the South African rooibos plant
Rich in minerals & flavonoids
High in healthy antioxidants
Anti-microbial properties


Our specially grown rooibos tea leaves are carefully ground down to form a fine powder. This enables you to consume all of the natural goodness.
We would describe the taste of PureChimp rooibos matcha, as naturally sweet with a slight nutty element.
What kind of goodness?
Our rooibos matcha tea is naturally caffeine-free, but still brimming with antioxidants, which are essential for flushing out potentially harmful free radicals, which can do damage to your health and your skin.
PureChimp rooibos matcha also has anti-microbial properties.
Why PureChimp Rooibos Matcha?







Pesticide-Free




South African Rooibos




100% Natural




5% Of Our Profits Go To Charity




Recyclable Glass Jar/Compostable Pouch




Taste Guarantee




Other details
For best results: Mix 1 level scoop/half a level tsp (around 1g) with a dash of cold water & whisk away. Top up with hot water and add a dash of milk if required.
Can be used with hot water/milk/juice/smoothies/baking.

details:

Don’t get us wrong, there are more exciting, interesting and special Colombians out there, but in terms of yumminess this one takes the trophy. ESPRESSO ROAST: Expect a bit more dark chocolate and marmalade. Milk brings out a malty character, but the orange still shines through.

name: Votch - Award winning vegan leather straps
description: Black & gold classic styled Piñatex Watch, Piñatex is an innovative sustainable material from pineapple leaf fibres.Piñatex is a by-product from the pineapple harvest and provides additional income for the farmers growing this wondrous fruit. No extra land, pesticides or fertilisers are used in the production of Piñatex, meaning our straps are not only good for animals, but for this beautiful planet we call home too.This unisex watch is fitted with quick release straps that are made of highly durable, vegan friendly materials and are easily interchangeable.Specification:Case Diameter - 38 mm.Case Colour - Brushed gold.Movement -Japanese GL20.Dial Colour- White with brushed gold indexes and handsStrap Colour - Black.Strap Material - Pinatex.Strap Width - 20 mm.Water Resistant - 3ATM.Wrist Fitting - approx. 170 - 210mm.Care instructions - Please be aware that as Piñatex is a natural material we recommend you take extra special care of it. To keep your strap in top condition we recommend using a natural wax such. It's best to leave the waxed strap in a warm location for 24 hours and then buff with a soft cloth. Then tell your strap you love it, because it came from pineapples and we think it deserves to be told.
details:
Black & gold classic styled Piñatex Watch, Piñatex is an innovative sustainable material from pineapple leaf fibres.

Piñatex is a by-product from the pineapple harvest and provides additional income for the farmers growing this wondrous fruit. No extra land, pesticides or fertilisers are used in the production of Piñatex, meaning our straps are not only good for animals, but for this beautiful planet we call home too.

This unisex watch is fitted with quick release straps that are made of highly durable, vegan friendly materials and are easily interchangeable.

Specification:

  • Case Diameter - 38 mm.
  • Case Colour - Brushed gold.
  • Movement -Japanese GL20.
  • Dial Colour- White with brushed gold indexes and hands
  • Strap Colour - Black.
  • Strap Material - Pinatex.
  • Strap Width - 20 mm.
  • Water Resistant - 3ATM.
  • Wrist Fitting - approx. 170 - 210mm.

Care instructions - Please be aware that as Piñatex is a natural material we recommend you take extra special care of it. To keep your strap in top condition we recommend using a natural wax such. It's best to leave the waxed strap in a warm location for 24 hours and then buff with a soft cloth. Then tell your strap you love it, because it came from pineapples and we think it deserves to be told.

details:
Our launch collection combines classic style and design across every timepiece. Each watch has a 38mm case with a vegan leather strap that will arrive to you in its own eco friendly felt pouch and box.

All watches are fitted with quick release straps that are made of highly durable, vegan friendly leather and are easily interchangeable. Our strap materials are free from PVC, heavy metals, flame retardants and have no added antimicrobial chemicals. They are produced with low VOC emissions and also incorporate recycled and renewable content.

Case Diameter 38 mm

Case Colour Brushed silver

Movement Japanese GL20

Dial Colour White with brushed silver indexes and hands

Strap Colour Black

Strap Material Vegan faux leather

Strap Width 20 mm

Water Resistant 3ATM

Wrist Fitting approx. 150 - 210mm

Compatible Straps: 20mm Watch Straps

Delievery methods and costs

Free worldwide shipping

Returns Policy

Our returns policy lasts a total of 30 days. If 30 days have gone by since your purchase, unfortunately we will be unable to offer you a refund or exchange.

We offer free returns on watch orders placed in the UK, to obtain your free returns label please contact jo@votch.co.uk

To be eligible for a return, your item must be unused and in the same condition that you received it. It must also be in the original packaging that is come in.

To complete your return, we require a receipt or proof of purchase.

Refunds

Once your return is received and checked over, we will send you an email to notify you that we have received your returned item. We will also notify you of the approval or rejection of your refund.

If all is ok, then your refund will be processed, and a credit will automatically be applied to your credit card or original method of payment, within a certain amount of days.

Late or missing refunds

If you haven’t received a refund yet, please keep a check on your bank account once you have had the approval of refund notification. Then the next step would be to contact your credit card company or bank, as it may take some time before your refund is officially posted.

If you’ve done all of this and you still have not received your refund yet, please contact us at helpme@votch.co.uk and we will be happy to help.

Sale items

For sale returns and exchanges, items must be returned within 14 days and the returns policy remains the same as full priced items as listed above.

Exchanges

Changed your mind on the colour? No worries! Send us an email to helpme@votch.co.uk with what you'd like to exchange it for and return your item to:

Votch at Evanwood, 17 Ronald Close, Kempston, Bedford, UK, MK42 7SH

Shipping

To return your product, you should mail your product to:

Votch at Evanwood, 17 Ronald Close, Kempston, Bedford, UK, MK42 7SH

We offer free watch returns from UK only currently - please email helpme@votch.co.uk where we will assist you with your return. For all other items / outside of the UK you will be responsible for paying for your own shipping costs for returning your item. Shipping costs are non-refundable. If you receive a refund, the cost of return shipping will be deducted from your refund.

Depending on where you live, the time it may take for your exchanged product to reach you, may vary.

If you are shipping an item over £50, we advise using a trackable shipping service or purchasing shipping insurance. We can’t guarantee that we will receive your returned item.

details:
We’ve all seen the images of plastic toothbrushes washing up on beaches all over the world. It’s such a sad sight to see and a huge problem in the fight against plastic pollution.

Let's be part of the solution rather than the problem? Make a simple swap. We have created our very own sustainable bamboo toothbrushes. The handle is made from 100% biodegradable Moso Bamboo. Moso is panda friendly because this particular bamboo species is not recognised as food by the pandas. Meaning you can keep your pearly whites sparkling clean without hurting any of our furry friends.

Refund policy

We have a 30-day return policy, which means you have 30 days after receiving your item to request a return.

To be eligible for a return, your item must be in the same condition that you received it, unused and in its original packaging. You’ll also need the receipt or proof of purchase.

To start a return, you can contact us at info@greenislandco.com and we’ll send you instructions on how and where to send your package. Items sent back to us without first requesting a return will not be accepted.

com.

Damages and issues

Please inspect your order upon reception and contact us immediately if the item is defective, damaged or if you receive the wrong item, so that we can evaluate the issue and make it right.

Exceptions / non-returnable items

Certain types of items cannot be returned, like custom products (such as special orders or personalized items), and personal care goods (such as beauty products). Please get in touch if you have questions or concerns about your specific item.

Exchanges

The fastest way to ensure you get what you want is to return the item you have, and once the return is accepted, make a separate purchase for the new item.

Refunds

We will notify you once we’ve received and inspected your return, and let you know if the refund was approved or not. If approved, you’ll be automatically refunded on your original payment method. Please remember it can take some time for your bank or credit card company to process and post the refund too.

name: Curl Up Organic Twill Robe
description:
Yawn’s new organic cotton robe is cut from our cosy luxury cotton. The relaxed silhouette can be cinched in with a self-tie belt at the waist. Other features include white piping on the cuffs, long sleeves, generous side pockets and a hanging loop made from our bespoke 'we have drift off' message tape. To create a classic, every detail counts.The Fabric 
Organic cotton twill (the cosy one). The very first fabric we developed, now available in an organic cotton twill. With its warmer handle, twill is pliable and drapes beautifully - just the right weight for chillier nights. Certified by GOTS, it uses 88% less water, 62% less energy and no toxic chemicals. If you feel the cold, wrap yourself in our cotton twill.The print
Every Yawn print is drawn or painted by hand in our studio in London, with hidden details for you to find, in your own time.Delivery & ReturnsDelivery InformationStandard Shipping - £6.92International Shipping - £15.68Returns Information

name: ENRICHD Heirloom Raw Chocolate Bars 60g
description:
By far the best chocolate on the entire planet.The cacao in these bars is from 200 years old Chuncho cacao trees that live (protected by the sacred Apu Urusayhua mountain) in Peru.Because they are raw, we are able to maintain high antioxidant levels along with the rich flavour of the beans.At an altitude of 1200m (unusual for cacao) these cacao trees are truly magical and I vividly remember the first time I enjoyed their offering.You see, when you eat chocolate from healthy, wise old trees there is something very special that is gifted to us, something completely intangible, that touches your heart and merges with your soul. Yes, this is deep living chocolate.

INGREDIENTS
EVERY single ingredient in these bars is purposely selected and is made by one of the World's finest chocolate makers Jacques Cop.

>> Cacao (un-roasted) from 200 year old Chuncho trees from the Urubamba Valley in Peru>> Lions Mane Mushroom (Dual Extract & Wood Grown)>> Reishi Mushroom (Dual Extract & Wood Grown)>> Wildcrafted Chaga Mushroom (Dual Extract & Wildcrafted)>> Coconut Palm Sugar>> Longan Powder

*Soy Free, Lecithin free, Nothing else added.Simple, potent and AMAZING! (See reviews below!)WHICH SHOULD YOU CHOOSE?LIONS MANE
= FOCUS CLARITY CREATIVITY
(Dual Extract & Wood Grown 🍄)REISHI
= CALM BALANCE IMMUNITY
(Dual Extract & Wood Grown 🍄)WILDCRAFTED CHAGA
= INVIGORATE PROTECT TRANSCEND
(Dual Extract & Wildcrafted 🍄)...you could always get the 3 bar bundle!ANCIENT CHUNCHO CACAO TREES
Peruvian Chuncho in its authentic and pure form is rare to say the least."Under the shadows of the Apu Urusayhua, Mother of stone, grow the old and sturdy Chuncho trees, some of which are 200 years old.

Local mythology describes Apu Urusayhua (mother of stone) as a sacred mountain. Apu is also the local name given to the mountain spirits that guard the land and connect the people to the highest realm.

Beneath the heights, the spume and the strong winds of the Apu Urusayhua lives the lush Urubamba Valley, where local smallholders grow their ancient Chuncho".Natives of the valley are proud of their heritage and to this day a number of families harvest the Chuncho beans from these beautiful and wise trees to make their own chocolate.

Cacao genetic scientists have found that, genetically speaking, these old Chunchos are some of the richest cacaos in the world.To preserve the genetic code of this cacao and the health of the land and to respect these beautiful trees our master chocolatier sources from selected farmers with old growth Chuncho trees.

You see why we chose these cacao trees and these beans now, right?We invite you to enjoy them....
details:
By far the best chocolate on the entire planet.

The cacao in these bars is from 200 years old Chuncho cacao trees that live (protected by the sacred Apu Urusayhua mountain) in Peru.

Because they are raw, we are able to maintain high antioxidant levels along with the rich flavour of the beans.

At an altitude of 1200m (unusual for cacao) these cacao trees are truly magical and I vividly remember the first time I enjoyed their offering.

You see, when you eat chocolate from healthy, wise old trees there is something very special that is gifted to us, something completely intangible, that touches your heart and merges with your soul. Yes, this is deep living chocolate.

INGREDIENTS
EVERY single ingredient in these bars is purposely selected and is made by one of the World's finest chocolate makers Jacques Cop.

>> Cacao (un-roasted) from 200 year old Chuncho trees from the Urubamba Valley in Peru

>> Lions Mane Mushroom (Dual Extract & Wood Grown)

>> Reishi Mushroom (Dual Extract & Wood Grown)

>> Wildcrafted Chaga Mushroom (Dual Extract & Wildcrafted)

>> Coconut Palm Sugar

>> Longan Powder

*Soy Free, Lecithin free, Nothing else added.

Simple, potent and AMAZING! (See reviews below!)

WHICH SHOULD YOU CHOOSE?

LIONS MANE
= FOCUS CLARITY CREATIVITY
(Dual Extract & Wood Grown 🍄)

REISHI
= CALM BALANCE IMMUNITY
(Dual Extract & Wood Grown 🍄)

WILDCRAFTED CHAGA
= INVIGORATE PROTECT TRANSCEND
(Dual Extract & Wildcrafted 🍄)

...you could always get the 3 bar bundle!

ANCIENT CHUNCHO CACAO TREES
Peruvian Chuncho in its authentic and pure form is rare to say the least.

"Under the shadows of the Apu Urusayhua, Mother of stone, grow the old and sturdy Chuncho trees, some of which are 200 years old.

Local mythology describes Apu Urusayhua (mother of stone) as a sacred mountain. Apu is also the local name given to the mountain spirits that guard the land and connect the people to the highest realm.

Beneath the heights, the spume and the strong winds of the Apu Urusayhua lives the lush Urubamba Valley, where local smallholders grow their ancient Chuncho".

Natives of the valley are proud of their heritage and to this day a number of families harvest the Chuncho beans from these beautiful and wise trees to make their own chocolate.

Cacao genetic scientists have found that, genetically speaking, these old Chunchos are some of the richest cacaos in the world.

To preserve the genetic code of this cacao and the health of the land and to respect these beautiful trees our master chocolatier sources from selected farmers with old growth Chuncho trees.

You see why we chose these cacao trees and these beans now, right?

We invite you to enjoy them....

name: BLACK & PIÑATEX | MOMENT
description: Our new, smaller 36mm collection comes with a 3 hand Japanese Quartz movement and our signature brushed metal casing. All watches are fitted with quick release straps that are made of highly durable, vegan friendly materials and are easily interchangeable. The straps on this Votch are created from Piñatex, an innovative and sustainable fabric created from pineapple leaf fibres (how amazing?!). Piñatex is a by-product from the pineapple harvest and provides additional income for the farmers growing this wondrous fruit. No extra land, pesticides or fertilisers are used in the production of Piñatex, meaning our straps are not only good for animals, but for this beautiful planet we call home too.Please be aware that as Piñatex is a natural material we recommend you take extra special care of it. To keep your strap in top condition we recommend using a natural wax such as the clear dubbin that is available here. It’s best to leave the waxed strap in a warm location for 24 hours and then buff with a soft cloth. Then tell your strap you love it, because it came from pineapples and we think it deserves to be told.Case Diameter 36 mmCase Colour Brushed blackCase Material Stainless steelMovement 3 hand Japanese Quartz movementDial Colour White with black indexes and handsStrap Colour BlackStrap Material PiñatexStrap Width 18 mmWater Resistant 3ATMWrist Fitting approx. 160 - 200mmCompatible Straps: 18mm Watch Straps
details:
Our new, smaller 36mm collection comes with a 3 hand Japanese Quartz movement and our signature brushed metal casing. All watches are fitted with quick release straps that are made of highly durable, vegan friendly materials and are easily interchangeable. The straps on this Votch are created from Piñatex, an innovative and sustainable fabric created from pineapple leaf fibres (how amazing?!). Piñatex is a by-product from the pineapple harvest and provides additional income for the farmers growing this wondrous fruit. No extra land, pesticides or fertilisers are used in the production of Piñatex, meaning our straps are not only good for animals, but for this beautiful planet we call home too.

Please be aware that as Piñatex is a natural material we recommend you take extra special care of it. To keep your strap in top condition we recommend using a natural wax such as the clear dubbin that is available here. It’s best to leave the waxed strap in a warm location for 24 hours and then buff with a soft cloth. Then tell your strap you love it, because it came from pineapples and we think it deserves to be told.

Case Diameter 36 mm

Case Colour Brushed black

Case Material Stainless steel

Movement 3 hand Japanese Quartz movement

Dial Colour White with black indexes and hands

Strap Colour Black

Strap Material Piñatex

Strap Width 18 mm

Water Resistant 3ATM

Wrist Fitting approx. 160 - 200mm

Compatible Straps: 18mm Watch Straps

name: test
Floor and Surface Lemon Gel Cleaner 5ltr
description:
Our EU Ecolabel accredited Multi Floor & Surface Gel Cleaner 5L Concentrate is ideal for mopping and general surface cleaning. This eco floor cleaner and surface cleaner, once diluted polishes to a shine and leaves your home clean and fresh with a delightful lemon fragrance. 
As a plant based, vegan friendly, eco floor cleaner and surface cleaner, it is suitable for hardwood floors, tile floors, laminate floors, slate and vinyl flooring. You can also use this eco friendly floor cleaner as a general surface cleaner across worktops, cabinets, sinks, tiles, doors and kitchen appliances. It is also safe to use on paintwork, metal surfaces, glass, rubber and through pressure and power washers.

Free from: Chrlorine Bleaches, Solvents, Formaldehyde, perfume and dyes, Lanolin, EDTAs, APEs and low VOCs
5 Litre Concentrate Floor Cleaner
Powerful degreaser
Citrus fresh odour leaves a light fragrance
Polishes to a shine
Safe in septic tanks if used as directed
Reduced impact on aquatic life
Reduced use of hazardous substances
Phosphate and phosphonate free
Safe in septic tanks if used as directed
Readily biodegradable

Areas of Use

Hard Floors - Tiles, hardwood, laminate, slate and vinyl flooring.
Kitchen Work Surfaces - Cabinets, worktops, sinks and tiles.
Kitchen appliances. 

Instructions for Use 
Apply a small amount to a damp cloth and wipe the surface. For heavy cleaning, apply directly onto the surface, leave to stand and wipe clean.

100% Made in Britain

details:
The Ocean Bottle’s flawless design makes it the perfect companion to avoid single-use plastic every day forever. Not to mention your ticket to becoming part of a movement dedicated to saving our oceans.

Impact:

With the sale of every Ocean Bottle we fund the collection of 11.4kg of plastic, equivalent to 1000 bottles before it enters the ocean, and improve social mobility at the same time.

With the help of partners Plastic Bank, funds go to places where plastic pollution is worst and tackle the 22mkgs of plastic pouring into the ocean each day.  Locals exchange plastic waste for digital tokens to spend on tuition, healthcare, tech goods, microfinance or money all via blockchain technology.

Features:

The Ocean bottle has been designed to last a lifetime, but don't take our word for it:  "If Apple designed a drinks container for life it would look like this." The Times, August 2020

Award-winning key features:

  • 500ml / 250g
  • Dishwasher safe
  • Dual opening for pouring drinks, ice and easy clean
  • Stainless steel Insulation for hot and cold drinks
  • Up-cycled ocean-bound plastic
  • Anti-leak
  • Easy carry loop

name: Show Me The Honey | Cherry & Toffee
description: Origin: El SalvadorRegion: ChalatenangoAltitude: 1450 maslVarietal: PacamaraProcess: HoneyFilter/Espresso: Filter RoastIn The Cup:Juicy sweet cherry & toffee vibes going onDescription:Congratulations you're still my agent! Loving this as a V60.Geek Notes:Chalatenango is not as well-known a region for coffee production as Santa Ana in El Salvador, but senior green-coffee buyer Piero Cristiani has spent years investing in and developing relationships with the community of smallholder farmers there in order to source some of the best, most dynamic coffees we've tasted. The average farm held by these producers is between 1–3 manzanas in size (1 manzana is slightly smaller than a hectare), and most yield fewer than 20 full-size bags of exportable coffee annually. They grow predominantly Bourbon, Pacas, and Pacamara variety coffees, and until the 2010s the producers with whom we're working had all been selling their lots on the local market for a low price, without any way to access better buyers.Delivery & ReturnsDelivery InformationStandard Shipping - £6.92International Shipping - £15.68Returns Information

Description:

Geek Notes:

Chalatenango is not as well-known a region for coffee production as Santa Ana in El Salvador, but senior green-coffee buyer Piero Cristiani has spent years investing in and developing relationships with the community of smallholder farmers there in order to source some of the best, most dynamic coffees we've tasted. The average farm held by these producers is between 1–3 manzanas in size (1 manzana is slightly smaller than a hectare), and most yield fewer than 20 full-size bags of exportable coffee annually. They grow predominantly Bourbon, Pacas, and Pacamara variety coffees, and until the 2010s the producers with whom we're working had all been selling their lots on the local market for a low price, without any way to access better buyers.

name: PLANALTO
description: GROWN BY: Sergio MantovaninniHINTS OF: Chocolate malt milkshakeROAST PROFILE: DarkWe refer to it as the Planalto estate for a reason: this is not a small farm. At a massive 908 hectares, with 430 hectares of coffee-producing land, Sergio and Mariza manage to produce around 12,000 bags a year - that’s 35 bags per hectare. A lot of coffee to go around! At a massive 908 hectares, with 430 hectares of coffee-producing land, Sergio and Mariza manage to produce around 12,000 bags a year - that’s 35 bags per hectare. A lot of coffee to go around! details:
Aesthetically intelligent, eye popping and brimming with versatility, Savu is a slice of classic WeAreNativ artistry. These leggings were created for Earth Beings who wish to proudly wear their Warrior Stripes in the form of fluid sweeping lines and futuristic asymmetrical shapes.

This sustainable piece has been ethically made using VITA POWER fabric from ECONYL® yarn which is regenerated from pre and post-consumer waste. Among its many talents, POWER is extremely hard wearing and durable (slow fashion box firmly ticked), it is sun cream, oil, chlorine resistant and has 50+ UV protection (yes, surfers!). POWER also has perfect muscular compression aimed at decreasing the production of lactic acid which boosts faster energy recovery. This really is the queen of high performance activewear fabrics - it is soft but sturdy, snug but stretchy, allowing you to bend, dance, run and sweat to your heart's content.

Model Carole is a size UK 8 and wears a size small Savu Leggings Black and Tan with a small Koro Top Black and is also pictured in a small Banda Top Black and Tan.

Designed in London, UK / Made ethically in Indonesia

Swimwear and leggings are a slightly different fit due to the nature of the garments, so you might be a different size - check the size chart in the guide below to make sure you’re choosing the correct size for you.

name: Salicylic Acid 2% Masque
description: Salicylic Acid 2% Masque is formulated to target lackluster tone and textural irregularities. The formula, infused with charcoal and clays, aims to enhance the appearance of smoothness and clarity, leaving the skin feeling refreshed. The structure of salicylic acid facilitates its lipophilicity and miscibility with the lipids located on the surface of the skin. It is a suitable ingredient for targeting the removal of dead skin cells on the surface of oily and blemish-prone skin, with the purpose of revealing more radiant skin beneath. Charcoal and clays are ingredients renowned for their deep cleansing abilities due to their porosity and large surface area available for adsorption. They aid the removal of facial impurities that would otherwise remain on the skin surface and clog pores. In comparison to Salicylic Acid 2% Solution, Salicylic Acid 2% Masque is a rinse-off formula. Leave on for no longer than 10 minutes in order to maximize the exfoliating benefits.

name: Glass & Stainless Steel Cleaner 700ml
description:
Our EU Ecolabel accredited Glass and Stainless Steel Cleaner leaves a sparkling, non-streaky and smear-free finish all around your home. As a glass cleaner spray, it can be used as a window cleaner and is suitable for internal and external glass. 
This plant based, vegan and eco friendly steel cleaner is alcohol free and easy to use, even in direct sunlight. You can use it as a streak free stainless steel cleaner on sinks, pans and appliances too. 

Low odour glass cleaner spray
Reduced use of hazardous substances
Phosphate and phosphonate free
Readily biodegradable
Safe in septic tanks if used as directed
Glass cleaner can be applied in direct sunlight
Quick drying stainless steel spray

Areas of Use 

Windows, glass and mirrors 
Chrome
Ceramic surfaces
Stainless steel 
Plastic surfaces

﻿Instructions for Use
Apply a small amount of the Glass and Stainless Steel Cleaner onto a damp cloth and wipe the surface. For heavy cleaning spray directly onto the surface, leave to stand for a few seconds and wipe clean. Try to use two separate cloths for application and polishing clean. Regular use will reduce usage and application time. Do not use on very hot surfaces.

name: Hand Sanitiser 5ltr
description:
Our anti-microbial, alcohol-free and anti-bacterial Hand Sanitiser cleans and kills germs and viruses preventing infection without the need for drying. Delphis Anti-Viral Hand Sanitiser has a twin chain Benzalkonium chloride quaternary ammonium-based biocide with broad activity spectrum against bacteria, moulds, yeasts, algae and enveloped viruses.

This plant based, vegan friendly hand sanitiser foam has high tolerance to organic soiling, hard water and anionic residues and good cleaning properties. The added moisturisers in the antibacterial hand sanitiser keeps hands soft and supple and doesn’t dry out skin like most alcohol products.

Higher bacterial and virus kill rate than most alcohol sanitisers.
Kills enveloped viruses
EN1276, EN1650, EN14476 approved

Our EU Ecolabel accredited Patio and Stone Cleaner 5L concentrate is a fast acting patio cleaner, removing deep stains, grease, soot, limescale, rust and efflorescence from exposed masonry, such as brickwork, stone, concrete, tiled or stone floors and walls, including granite and porcelain. It is also suitable to use as a headstone cleaner. 

As a vegan and plant friendly patio cleaner, our large 5 litre concentrate requires diluting before use and is ideal and safe to use both outdoors and indoors as stone cleaner on tiles and stone floors. 

  • Free from Petroleum solvent, Hydrochloric acid, VOCs,
    Formaldehyde, Alkylphenol Ethoxylates (APEs)
  • Fast acting patio stone cleaner
  • 5L Masonry & Brick Cleaner
  • Safe to use indoors
  • Effective in hard and soft water
  • Safe in septic tanks if used as directed
  • Reduced impact on aquatic life
  • Reduced use of hazardous substances
  • Phosphate and phosphonate free
  • Safe in septic tanks if used as directed
  • Readily biodegradable

Areas of Use

  • Brickwork and Masonry

  • Stone Walls and Floors

Instructions for Use

This 5ltr stone cleaner product is a concentrate and must be diluted prior to use. 

Once diluted, apply the patio stone cleaner to the surface by spray or brush and leave to stand. For heavy soiling allow 10-15 minutes contact time and agitate. For larger surface areas such as floors, use a mop and bucket. Rinse well with clean water. This product is not intended for large-scale cleaning.

name: Reusable Face Mask Filters - Pack of 10
description:
Delphis Eco face mask filters are designed to be used with our black or white reusable face masks. They are made for optimal filtration whilst being easy to breathe through. 
Each face mask filter is 2.4mm thick needle punched polyester, non-woven and this  provides the primary filtration of the face mask. The random orientation of the non-woven fibres in the filter creates a fibrous web to trap particles and give the best filtration without making it hard to breathe. This non-woven filter is traditionally used as one of the filtration layers in N95 masks. 

Pack of 10 reusable face mask filters, for use with Delphis Eco Face Masks. 
Reusable face mask filters, made for optimal filtration with ultimate breathability.
Each face mask filter is 2.4mm thick offering great filtration.

name: Shou Puerh Tea "The Grounding" (Organic)
description:
This is fantastic LOOSE LEAF SHOU PUERH tea is sourced from some of the cleanest mountains in Yunnan and is grown organically. 
It is ideally enjoyed a little after a meal though can be drank at any time.
Because of the fermentation this tea is naturally lower in caffeine than you'd expect.
TASTE OF SHOU PUERH
Earthy (over bitter)
This is a deep earthy tea, unlike green tea because it fermented for weeks in a specific environment for supporting the aging of the tea. Shoud puerh became a "new" category of tea after years of trying to speed up the aging process of sheng puerh tea. Shou Puerh could be thought of as a magnificent accident.
WHY SHOU PUERH?
- Grounding in Nature
- Digestive Support
- Calming in Nature
- Support the metabolism
ENRICHD always stands for the highest integrity when it comes to all of our teas, foods and sourcing. Tea is something we LOVE here and so we take extra measures to make sure this is some of the cleanest tea available.HOW TO PREPARE AND DRINK:1) Use approximately 1 tablespoon of tea.Add more or less depending on how you like your tea.2) Rinse the leaves in hot (just less than boiling) water.Literally leave the water on the leaves for a few seconds, then give that water to your garden.3) Steep the leaves in about 1/2 pint of water, and serve yourself and friends.Ideally use tea pot or side-handle tea pot but a strainer or cafetiere will work too. OR even loose in the bowl (see photos)TEA STEEPING TIPS:1) If you like your tea strong add more leaves and or increase the steeping time.2) You can steep each serving of these leaves more than once.3) Give yourself a minute to enjoy these leaves in silence if you can...
details:
This is fantastic LOOSE LEAF SHOU PUERH tea is sourced from some of the cleanest mountains in Yunnan and is grown organically. 

It is ideally enjoyed a little after a meal though can be drank at any time.

Because of the fermentation this tea is naturally lower in caffeine than you'd expect.

TASTE OF SHOU PUERH

Earthy (over bitter)

This is a deep earthy tea, unlike green tea because it fermented for weeks in a specific environment for supporting the aging of the tea. Shoud puerh became a "new" category of tea after years of trying to speed up the aging process of sheng puerh tea. Shou Puerh could be thought of as a magnificent accident.

WHY SHOU PUERH?

- Grounding in Nature

- Digestive Support

- Calming in Nature

- Support the metabolism


ENRICHD always stands for the highest integrity when it comes to all of our teas, foods and sourcing. Tea is something we LOVE here and so we take extra measures to make sure this is some of the cleanest tea available.

HOW TO PREPARE AND DRINK:
1) Use approximately 1 tablespoon of tea.
Add more or less depending on how you like your tea.

2) Rinse the leaves in hot (just less than boiling) water.
Literally leave the water on the leaves for a few seconds, then give that water to your garden.

3) Steep the leaves in about 1/2 pint of water, and serve yourself and friends.
Ideally use tea pot or side-handle tea pot but a strainer or cafetiere will work too. OR even loose in the bowl (see photos)

TEA STEEPING TIPS:
1) If you like your tea strong add more leaves and or increase the steeping time.

2) You can steep each serving of these leaves more than once.

3) Give yourself a minute to enjoy these leaves in silence if you can...

name: Men's Work / Boot Sock
description:
PRODUCT DETAILS
WORK BOOT SOCK – THICK, BLACK (OR GREY) COOLING COMFORT.
Our Work Boot Sock is built to make long days on your feet just a little more bearable. These thick, luxurious socks pair perfectly with work boots, walking boots, or even après ski boots. Minimising dampness and with added thermo-regulating properties, feet are kept cool, cushioned and dry all day long.
Why Bamboo?
Why Bamboo Fabric Work Socks?
Boody creates affordable luxury by crafting everyday essentials and underwear from viscose derived from bamboo. The result is a silky smooth base layer that keeps you cool and comfortable with seam-free stretch. Our bamboo fabric maintains it’s shape and is great for sensitive skin. Bamboo fibers are naturally smooth and round with no sharp spurs to irritate skin. Try the cooling comfort of the Boody Work Boot Crew Sock for yourself. We’re certain you’ll buy a pair for every day of the work week.
FEATURES & FIT

Crew length
Thicker knit
Soft, ribbed opening for comfort
Naturally breathable

 

FABRIC & CARE


Care: Machine wash and dry according to instructions on the care label using a mild, eco-friendly laundry detergent.
Content: 80% viscose made from organically grown bamboo, 17% nylon, 3% elastane

Harvested in FSC-certified fields in the Sichuan Province of China, our organically grown bamboo is used to create our signature soft and durable fabric. Boody is naturally breathable, antibacterial, thermo-regulating and hypoallergenic for pure comfort all day long.

name: Motivate Full-Length High-Waist Tights
description:
PRODUCT DETAILS
In a Boody first, we've developed a brand new fabric blending two organic and sustainable yarns to bring you a new active tight. Organic Bamboo gives this active tight lightweight breathability and a flexible stretch while the Organic Cotton rounds the fabric off to create an ultra-comfortable fit.Get your body moving in our Motivate Full-Length High-Waist Tights. name: Goodnight Night Dress
description:
PRODUCT DETAILS
THE GOODNIGHT NIGHT DRESS – LIGHT AND AIRY LONG SLEEP SHIRT.
We spend half our time sleeping. Why not do it in comfort? The Goodnight Nightdress is silky-soft and available in either Dove or Dusty Pink. A cozy bedtime staple you'll wear night after night, this nightdress ticks all the right boxes when it comes to drifting off to sleep in luxury. Women's nighties are at their best when lightweight, comfy and breathable. Made from our signature viscose derived from bamboo blend, this nightdress ticks all the above boxes.
Featuring a wide neckband detail with a tonal cover-stitch, curved hemline, flattering centre-back seam detail and soft extended sleeve, you'll fall head over heels for this must-have nightie. With its wide arm opening, loose fit and soft jersey fabric, this nightdress is a dream come true. Wrap up in our cozy Knit Wrap and slip on a pair of our Chunky Bed Sock to put the final touches on your sleep-time style.
Boody Lounge is coming up on the large size. We suggest you order the next size down.
FEATURES & FIT

Boody Lounge is coming up on the large size. We suggest you order the next size down.
Wide neckband & arm openings
Curved hemline
Loose fit
Center back seam detail

 
Why Bamboo?
Why Bamboo Lounge Nightdress?
Boody creates affordable luxury by building everyday essentials and underwear from viscose derived from bamboo. The result is a silky smooth base layer that keeps you cool and comfortable with seam-free stretch. Our bamboo fabric maintains it’s shape and is great for sensitive skin. Bamboo fibers are naturally smooth and round with no sharp spurs to irritate skin. Try the cooling comfort of the Boody Lounge Nightdress for yourself. We know they’ll quickly become one of your go-to styles.
FABRIC & CARE



Care: Machine wash and dry according to instructions on the care label using a mild, eco-friendly laundry detergent.


Content: 95% viscose made from organically-grown bamboo, 5% elastane
Harvested in FSC-certified fields in the Sichuan Province of China, our organically grown bamboo is used to create our signature soft and durable fabric. Boody is naturally breathable, antibacterial, thermo-regulating and hypoallergenic for pure comfort all day long.

description:

PADDED SHAPER BRA – SMOOTH AND SEAMLESS WITH EXTRA SHAPE AND SUPPORT.
Added by popular demand, our seam free Padded Shaper Crop (with removable inserts) pulls on with ease, feels wonderfully comfortable and has the extra support and comfort every woman searches for in a bra. We’ve done away with all the nasty things – the straps that dig in, the tricky fastenings and the wires. The Padded Shaper Bra delivers style, comfort, and support. You’ll never want to take it off!
We are donating 1% of all bra sales to Breast Cancer UK
Mommy Feedback:  "If I could have one bra to wear while pregnant and post-partum, it would be this one."  With no wires or clasps paired with supremely soft material, the shaper bras make the ins and outs of nursing access a breeze.
